Unify into one frontend system; remove old Supabase app

Completes the merge of the two systems into a single frontend-only CRM built on
the Telesales → Direct Sales → Credit pipeline.

Pipeline UX:
- LeadWorkDrawer: stage/role-aware actions — call attempts (3-no-answer
  auto-close), telesales qualify form (→ Direct Sales), DS document link +
  submit-to-credit, dispositions, self-reminders. Wired into the agent queue.
- SupervisorQueue (Telesales + Direct Sales): stage-filtered live queue with
  assignment to the team's agents.
- Credit decisions queue (approve/reject).
- Analytics (funnel + status distribution), Attendance board, Duplicate
  detection — all computed from the mock service.
- Role-aware nav + roleHome route each role to its portal.

Cleanup (one clean frontend for handoff):
- Deleted the old Supabase app: app/telesales, app/direct-sales, app/admin,
  app/login, app/forgot-password, app/reset-password, app/api, actions/,
  lib/supabase, lib/sla, lib/assignment, lib/phone, lib/preview, types/,
  supabase/ migrations, old components (telesales/direct-sales/admin/analytics/
  shared except BrandLogo), and hooks/.
- Repo now contains only the /crm frontend backed by lib/crm/service.ts
  (localStorage mock — the single seam the backend team replaces).

